Next I’ll update `J23`, save the workbook to the output directory with the same filename, and verify that the formula was written correctly.
Code:
```repl
import os
from openpyxl import load_workbook

input_path = input_spreadsheet
filename = os.path.basename(input_path)
output_path = os.path.join("/sandbox/output/output_spreadsheet", filename)

wb = load_workbook(input_path)
ws = wb["Deal 8"]

# Set the correct formula
ws["J23"] = '=IF(I12="","",I12)'

wb.save(output_path)

# Verify
check_wb = load_workbook(output_path, data_only=False)
check_ws = check_wb["Deal 8"]
print({
    "output_exists": os.path.exists(output_path),
    "sheet": check_ws.title,
    "I12": check_ws["I12"].value,
    "J23_formula": check_ws["J23"].value,
})
```
